  4. NNAR(Neaural Network Autoregression Model)
  • NNAR(p, k): p time lag, k-hidden layers
  1. NNAR(Neaural Network Autoregression Model on a Seasonal Dataset)
  • NNAR(p, P, k): p time lag, k-hidden layers, P seasonal leg
  • NNAR(9, 1, 5): 9 time lag, 4-hidden layers, 1 seasonal leg

# install.packages('forecast')
data <- read.csv('./data/APTelectricity.csv')
myts <- ts(data$watt, frequency = 288)

set.seed(34)
fit = nnetar(myts)

# forecast
nnet_forecast <- forecast(fit, h=400, PI=F)
library(ggplot2)
autoplot(nnet_forecast)

fit2 <- nnetar(myts, xreg=data$appliances)
y <- rep(2, times=12*10)
nnet_forecat2 <- forecast(fit2, xreg=y, PI=F)
autoplot(nnet_forecat2)

library(caTools)
split <- sample.split(scaled$medv, SplitRatio = 0.7)
train_data <- subset(scaled, split==T)
test_data <- subset(scaled, split==F)

# install.packages('neuralnet')
library(neuralnet)
name <- names(train_data)
fomula <- as.formula(paste("medv~", paste(name[!name %in% "medv"], collapse = "+")))

nn <- neuralnet(fomula, data=train_data, hidden=c(5, 3), linear.output = T)
plot(nn)

?compute
## Help on topic 'compute' was found in the following packages:
## 
##   Package               Library
##   dplyr                 /Library/Frameworks/R.framework/Versions/3.6/Resources/library
##   neuralnet             /Library/Frameworks/R.framework/Versions/3.6/Resources/library
## 
## 
## Using the first match ...
predict_nn_value <- compute(nn, test_data[1:13]) # Except medv
predctions <- predict_nn_value$net.result * (max(data$medv) - min(data$medv)) + min(data$medv)
test <- test_data$medv * (max(data$medv) - min(data$medv)) + min(data$medv)

MSE.nn <- sum((test - predctions)^2) / nrow(test_data)
error_df <- data.frame(test, predctions)

library(ggplot2)
ggplot(error_df, aes(x=test, y=predctions)) + geom_point() + stat_smooth()
## `geom_smooth()` using method = 'loess' and formula 'y ~ x'
